  "local_port": 53222,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "I am already using Reliance Jio SIM card. How to check data usage on the same ?",
  "response": "To check your data usage on a Reliance Jio SIM card, you have several options:\n\n### Using MyJio App:\n\n1. **Download and Install**:\n   - If you don\u2019t already have the MyJio app installed, download it from the Google Play Store (for Android) or the Apple App Store (for iOS).\n\n2. **Login**:\n   - Open the MyJio app and login using your Jio number and OTP.\n\n3. **Check Data Usage**:\n   - Once logged in, on the home screen, you will see a summary of your data usage, including remaining data and the validity period.\n\n### Using Jio Website:\n\n1. **Visit Jio Website**:\n   - Go to [Jio's Official Website](https://www.jio.com).\n\n2. **Login**:\n   - Login using your Jio number and OTP.\n\n3. **Check Data Usage**:\n   - Once logged in, navigate to the \u2018My Account\u2019 section to view your data usage details.\n\n### Using USSD Codes:\n\n1. **Dial Code**:\n   - Open your phone\u2019s dialer and dial *333#.\n\n2. **Follow Instructions**:\n   - You will receive a menu on the screen. Follow the instructions to get your data balance.\n\n### Through SMS:\n\n1. **Send SMS**:\n   - Send an SMS with the text \u2018MBAL\u2019 to 55333 from your Jio number.\n\n2. **Receive SMS**:\n   - You will receive a SMS detailing your data balance.\n\n### Other Methods:\n\n1. **Reliance Jio Customer Care**:\n   - Call Jio customer care at 1991 and follow the IVR instructions to know your data usage.\n\n2. **Data Usage Settings**:\n   - You can also check the data usage through your mobile phone's settings. This method will give you a general overview but might not be as accurate as the official sources.\n\nBy following any of these methods, you should be able to keep track of your data usage effectively on your Reliance Jio SIM card.",
